      "date": "2014-05-20 07:01:02.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n\"what's your thoughts on backward compatibility ?\"\n\nOld llog doesn't have valid bit stored, and the validity (padding) field should be zero, so when we see zero validity field in llog rec, we assume it's an old llog and have both LA_UID & LA_GID.",
